solutions.content:
Since in bst value less than root are to left and greater than root are to right, we make use of it.

If the value of root is equal to anyone of p & q it means it is LCA since second value will be velow it.
Else we check if both value lie on left and right side, then in this case root will be LCA since both are on different side.
In case if both values are on same side, we check which side do they belong to and pass that to our function

```
class Solution {
public:
    TreeNode* lowestCommonAncestor(TreeNode* root, TreeNode* p, TreeNode* q) {
         if(!root){
            return NULL;
        }
        if(root->val==p->val || root->val==q->val)
            return root;
        if(root->val<max(p->val,q->val) && root->val>min(p->val,q->val)){
            return root;
        }
        // both are less than root then lca is left side
        else if(root->val >max(p->val,q->val)){
            return lowestCommonAncestor(root->left,p,q);
        }
        else
            return lowestCommonAncestor(root->right,p,q);
    }
};
```

